			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Stretching things vertically is a standard raster effect and requires nothing more than the ability to change the scrolling values as the screen is drawn. (vis: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raster_bar" class="postlink">wikipedia:Rasterbars</a>, <a href="http://www.pouet.net/prod.php?which=2048" class="postlink">pouet:Copper by Surprise!</a>).<br /><br />In some instances (e.g. VGA compatible hardware) vertical stretching is additionally a natively supported operation of the hardware, without needing any CPU involvement.<br /><br />Stretching things horizontally requires a little more help from the graphics unit. I doubt the NES provides enough rope.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

