			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">infidelity wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm assuming $2000 &amp; $2001 need to be used?</div><br /><br />Nope. That's what lazigamer meant by no hardware functionality. Vertical stretching is accomplished by manipulating scroll registers, but you can't use the same technique for horizontal stretching.<br /><br />If you're writing a homebrew, you would probably need to design it from the ground up carefully and with the horizontal stretching in mind. You could &quot;stretch&quot; the image one of two ways. You could manipulate the nametable (re-assign tile numbers) to widen objects on the screen, either expanding them one tile at a time, or by using multiple similar tiles that are increasingly wide. Or, you could manipulate the pattern table. If you're using CHR RAM, you would modify the pixel data to gradually increase the width of the graphics. If you're using CHR ROM, you would have all the frames pre-drawn and cycle CHR banks in a manner similar to the way Metal Storm achieves parallax scrolling.<br /><br />In other words, you would have to fake it one way or another.<br /><br />If you're working on a hack, adding in a horizontal stretching affect would probably be more work than it is worth.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

