				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you can make a pattern that repeats vertically (e.g. a checkerboard), you could build a single nametable that has one row of the pattern at each of several stretched widths. This would let you use a repeated vertical split scroll to tile the pattern over all or part of the screen without having to dedicate the entire nametable, allowing you to progressively &quot;stretch&quot; the pattern just by adjusting the vertical srcoll position used during vertical tiling, without having to upload any new nametable data between frames.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

